	   <a name=99586296987481></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99586296987481><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>spell book</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=53540><span id= >Sabutant</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>12 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jul 23rd 12:36 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.66]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I just made it to lvl 29! I usually group, but don't mind a little soloing from time to time. The problem is- So many spells!&nbsp;&nbsp;   Any thoughts on how to best organize my spell book for efficient usage? I have all the spells available to a lvl 29 Shammie, somewhere around 70 or so. that's a lot of spells to keeep track of. Thanks a bunch<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=99633312440571></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99633312440571><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=99633312440571>RE: spell book</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=99633312440571#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=22327><span id= >Nolewen</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>6 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Jul 28th 11:12 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I see so many people these days asking how to organize spell books! And Badjur's right: it has more to do with the player than the game. But no one seems to mention this method, yet I find it useful:<br><br>Place all of your "hot swap" spells -- usually buffs -- on the first pages. For example, you don't often have Cure Poison up, but you might want it handy and not have to go turning page after page looking for it.&nbsp;&nbsp;Even hotkeying "/book 17" requires you to look for the hotkey while the poison is eating away at your victim. Putting it on the first page usually allows you drop, mem, stand and cast quickly.<br><br>Place your "standard line-up" of spells on pages 3 & 4.  Or somewhere farther back and hotkey it. Basically what I go for here is when I die, all the spells I'm going to re-mem are on the same page/screen. Also, having them handy is a follow-up to the first tip. Now that you've cast your buff/cure, you'll want to put the old spell back.<br><br>For me, after these two setups, it's prety much pot-luck, although I tend to try and group similar spells together (poisons, debuffs, buffs, etc).<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>

</ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=9959266711066></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9959266711066><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=9959266711066>RE: spell book</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=9959266711066#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jul 23rd 6:17 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Pages 1-3 (the fifteen spells you load the most) (recommend -since it's almost two full sets and one or two spells will belong in both- making it one soloing set and one grouping set.)<br><br>Page 4 Blank<br><br>pages 5 onward... done by level, icon of spell, spell type (alt, abj, etc), whatever works for you<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
